You don&#x27;t get it.<p>First of all you don&#x27;t NEED most of the stuff shown there. The boilerplate at the bottom is there to cover EVERY POSSIBLE THING anyone would possibly ever want to do with unicode in Perl and because tchrist thinks it&#x27;s funny to do such things. If all you want is to read a unicode file, change its contents, then write it back to hdd without breaking encoding, you don&#x27;t need more than:<p><pre><code>    use utf8;
    use IO::All -utf8;
</code></pre>
Secondly, all other languages do it worse than Perl 5.
